{"id":90777,"title":"[Anti-osteoporosis drugs based on the guidelines for the Prevention and Treatment of Osteoporosis (2011 edition) ].","abstract":"The aim of osteoporosis treatment is to reduce fracture risk. Many kinds of anti-osteoporosis drugs are available in these days, and most of them increase bone mineral density and reduce the risk of fractures. Japanese 2011 guidelines for prevention and treatment of osteoporosis documents the recommendation level of each osteoporosis drugs. It is important to select drugs appropriate for each osteoporosis patient considering the mechanisms of drug action and their clinical efficiency. ","date":"2014-02-28","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24576937","annotations":[{"name":"Osteoporosis","weight":0.910027,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osteoporosis"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.767658,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.723263,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.652616,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Mineral","weight":0.546519,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mineral"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.542761,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Fracture","weight":0.52085,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fracture"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.469579,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Bone","weight":0.404766,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.386358,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Bone density","weight":0.105556,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone_density"},{"name":"Population density","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_density"},{"na